---
import GeminiLayout from "../../layouts/GeminiLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/quickstart-shared.css";
---

<GeminiLayout
  title="Gemini CLI Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes"
  description="Install Gemini CLI, authenticate, and leverage 1M token context to analyse your entire codebase in one shot."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="qs-wrapper">

    <header class="qs-hero">
      <span class="qs-hero__eyebrow">Gemini CLI · Getting Started</span>
      <h1 class="qs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="qs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="qs-hero__desc">Google's AI CLI with a 1M token context window. Feed it an entire codebase, a full log file, or a massive dataset — it can handle it.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="qs-journey">

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">01</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Prerequisites</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Node.js 18+ and a Google account</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">You can auth with your Google account on first launch (browser-based), or use a Gemini API key from aistudio.google.com.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>node --version</code></div>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">02</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Install</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Install Gemini CLI globally</h2>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>npm install -g @google/gemini-cli</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Verify: gemini --version</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">03</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Authenticate</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">First launch — browser auth or API key</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Run <code>gemini</code> and it will open a browser for Google account auth. Or skip the browser by setting an API key first.</p>
        <span class="qs-cmd-label">Option A — Google account (browser)</span>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>gemini</code></div>
        <span class="qs-cmd-label">Option B — API key (faster, better for scripts)</span>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>export GEMINI_API_KEY=your-key && gemini</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Get an API key free at aistudio.google.com/apikey</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step qs-step--active">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">04</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">First Real Task</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Non-interactive one-shot mode</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Use -p for scripting — non-interactive, returns output immediately. Perfect for piping in files.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>gemini -p "what does this codebase do and what are the main entry points" &lt; README.md</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Or pipe any file. With 1M context, you can pipe entire codebases.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="qs-milestone">
      <span class="qs-milestone__eyebrow">First Real Task</span>
      <h2 class="qs-milestone__title">Feed it your entire codebase — it can take it</h2>
      <p class="qs-milestone__desc">Most tools are bottlenecked by context. Gemini isn't. Use this to get a comprehensive analysis of your whole project at once.</p>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">1</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Navigate to your project root.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">2</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Run a security audit across the whole codebase:</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>find . -name "*.ts" -not -path "*/node_modules/*" | xargs cat | gemini -p "security audit: find auth issues, injection vectors, and exposed secrets"</code></div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">3</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Gemini processes the full codebase in one shot and returns a structured security report. No other CLI handles this scale.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="qs-next">
      <p class="qs-next__title">What next?</p>
      <div class="qs-next__grid">
        <a href="/gemini-cli/tips/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚡</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Tips & Tricks</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">--yolo mode, checkpointing, sandbox, GEMINI_MODEL env.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/gemini-cli/cheatsheet/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">📋</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Cheatsheet</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">All flags and workflows at a glance.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/gemini-cli/changelog/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">🔔</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Changelog</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Every Google release, tracked.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/gemini-cli/configs/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚙️</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Configs</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Models, sandbox settings, policy engine.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.qs-cmd').forEach(function(block) {
      var btn = document.createElement('button');
      btn.className = 'qs-cmd__copy';
      btn.textContent = 'copy';
      btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var code = block.querySelector('code');
        if (!code) return;
        var text = code.textContent.replace(/^\$\s*/, '').trim();
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function() {
          btn.textContent = 'copied!';
          setTimeout(function() { btn.textContent = 'copy'; }, 1500);
        });
      });
      block.style.paddingRight = '5rem';
      block.appendChild(btn);
    });
  </script>
</GeminiLayout>
